Gauteng Premier, David Makhura, announced that some sections of Charlotte Maxeke Hospital will open on Monday. Gauteng Infrastructure Development MEC, Tasneem Motara, explains #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura announced that parts of Charlotte Maxeke Hospital that are structurally intact will be reopened. Plans are in place to reopen the oncology unit. READ: Petition to reopen Charlotte Maxeke Hospital Gauteng Infrastructure Development MEC, Tasneem Motara, says several changes have been made. Municipality officials will inspect the unit on Friday. The hospital was closed two months ago after a fire broke out. Watch the video above for more details on this story. The Gauteng Provincial Command Council, led by Premier David Makhura, is giving an update on Covid-19 in the province. It will cover the comprehensive health response following the sharp increase in infections.